articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Under the agreement worked out with Egyptian and Qatari mediators and backed by the United States, Israel was meant to allow Palestinians displaced from the homes in the north to return to their homes.
articles.title: Thousands wait to return to northern Gaza, Trump urges Jordan, Egypt to take Palestinians

articles.author: Nandita Bose, Kanishka Singh
articles.description: A Hamas official reacted with suspicion to the remarks, echoing longstanding Palestinian fears about being driven permanently from their homes.
articles.title: Trump says Jordan, Egypt should take more Palestinians from Gaza

articles.author: Fatos Bytyci, Florion Goga
articles.description: Ali Amini was just days from starting a new life in the United States when President Donald Trump halted aid for resettling Afghan refugees last week, a move that Amini worries could put his life in danger if forced to return home.
articles.title: Trump aid freeze strands Afghan visa holders in Albania

articles.author: Luciana Magalhaes
articles.description: Brazil's Ministry of Foreign Affairs plans to seek explanations from the U.S. government over the "degrading treatment" of Brazilians on a deportation flight, the ministry wrote on X on Saturday night.
articles.title: Brazil to demand explanations on 'degrading treatment' of deportees

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Insurrection is one of the few criminal charges from which a South Korean president does not have immunity. It is punishable by life imprisonment or death, although South Korea has not executed anyone in decades.
articles.title: South Korea's prosecutors indict President Yoon for insurrection

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Malawi and Uruguay said four of their troops were killed in clashes in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo against Rwandan-backed rebels, bringing the death toll among United Nations and southern African peacekeepers to at least 13 by Sunday.
articles.title: UN peacekeeper death toll in eastern Congo rises to six

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The United Nation's Palestinian refugee agency said on Sunday it had been ordered by Israel to vacate premises and cease all of its operations in occupied East Jerusalem by Thursday.
articles.title: UN agency UNRWA says Israel orders it to stop East Jerusalem operations this week

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli fire wounded five people in south Lebanon on Sunday, Lebanese media and security sources said, as residents sought to return to homes in the border area where Israeli forces remained on the ground after a deadline for their withdrawal passed.
articles.title: Israeli fire wounds five in south Lebanon as residents try to return, Lebanese media reports

articles.author: Mark Trevelyan
articles.description: Belarusians voted on Sunday in an election that was set to hand another five years in power to President Alexander Lukashenko, a close ally of Russia's Vladimir Putin.
articles.title: West cries foul over Belarus election as Lukashenko eyes seventh term

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.N. human rights experts and activists on Sunday condemned the arrest of an American, pro-Palestinian journalist in the Swiss city of Zurich, saying it raised concerns about freedom of speech.
articles.title: UN experts decry arrest of pro-Palestinian American journalist in Switzerland
